Example

 If you want an example, look first at the text
 files in:

   GenHTML/doc/txt/

 These are the raw text documents used to build this
 HTML, no changes or formatting was required in
 to the raw text documenta.


 Try it

  If you want, you can try building another copy
  of this documentation. 

  First, cd to the GenHTML directory:

    cd GenHTML

  Now, we will build a copy of the documentation
  in a directory named doc_copy, we will first
  create a single file version of the HTML:

    php GenHTML --i doc/txt/index --o doc_copy

  This will create a single index.html file in
  doc_copy using the default templates.

  If you want to build it in a multi-page format
  use the -m switch:

    php GenHTML --i doc/txt/index --o doc_copy -m

  Play about with options like:

    --link-depth 1

  And:

    --link-depth 2

  To see how it affects the navigation sections
  of each page.

